As for the whole Christmas/ X-mas thing, I find it rather interesting, as I never gave much thought to it. I think it's kind of retarded to call it X-mas if you don't believe/ care about Christ: the &quot;mas&quot; part still originally referred to &quot;mass&quot; or church services. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  If you don't like calling it Christmas than call it Solstice, since that was it it was originally called. This is not to say the following is wrong or &quot;gay&quot; or anything...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I don't really consider Christmas as a holiday celebrating the birth of christ. It might have been a long ass time ago, but nowadays it's for giftgiving and spending ludicrous amounts of cash. I'm an aetheist and I celebrate 'x-mas'.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
