<br>
Christmas currently, for MANY people, is celebrated almost totally as a holiday of giving gifts rather than as a holiday celebrating the birth of Christ.  The entire nature of the holiday has no relation at all to what it was originally termed for, so people calling it Xmas may be their way of naming it a different holiday than what it was originally meant to be.  However, they don't realize that (Christians included, and myself included until I did the background info earlier in the thread) that Xmas was actually coined to be the exact same meaning as Christmas.  They merely use the term because of ignorance, and considering the significance of the X no longer means much to us anymore, it seems pretty widely accepted that Xmas is removing Christ from Christmas for those who are not Christians. <br>
<br>
I disagree with you in stating that denying Christ is related to Christmas is a stupid idea, considering the current incarnation of the holiday of giving gifts has absolutely nothing to do with its first form, and was something adopted later on due to the generousity of St. Nicholas to children and the poor.  Also, I read on a few websites that historically it's been said that Christ was born in the spring time, not December.  So there's nothing wrong with not wanting to recognize the day as being related to Christ. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kerai>Kerai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Teh Anti-American</span><br>  Posts: 4756<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/27/03 10:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2102.topic&index=57>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.sowned.com/bleh/kerai2.gif height=77 width=69></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Because Stupidity is Amusing</span><hr size=1> It doesn't really matter Ant, christmas is inherently related to Christ. If you don't realize it, your education sucks.<br>
